default&#xa0; 
defaultThe methodology I will be using to connect demand to services applies 
defaultan Origin and Destination concept in order to create a series of lines on a map (Routes) which connect areas of residents (Origins) to a service such as a school, doctors, retail park etc. (Destinations).  
defaultThe previous chapters provide detailed research in
defaultto the level of demand that could be expected for a public transport network in the East Riding area. Using this information as well as micro data, it is possible to draw conclusions as to where public transport routes would be best placed to serve the pub
defaultlic need.
