default3.9.
default&#xa0; 
defaultBy repeating this process for all the difference services, and then combining the information, a network that provides access to the range of different services can be establish
defaulted. The gaps present in this network could be filled by alternative modes of transport such as Community Transport Operators and Dial-a-Ride services. The blue, green and purple lines are particularly important to the network as these segments of road conn
defaultect residents to different services, and if a bus route was put onto this section then it would fulfil the accessibility needs for various different user groups to different key services. The yellow lines indicate where a route is required in order to tran
defaultsport residents to one specific key service. In conjunction with the colour importance grading of each of these route sections, it is also important to consider other aspects of the transport network such as major settlement locations, estimated population
defaults and potential ridership levels. 
